# Airport API

Expore the APIs in the interactive documentation below

To get started, you need to create an [Application](http://example.net/) which will provide you with the API key you need to authenticate calls from your application.

## Airports Info by Code [/airports/{airportCode}?user_key={user_key}]

This operation returns information about the given airport code. The code must be the 3 letter IATA code.

+ Parameters

   + airportCode - the custer account ID
   + user_key - a key provisioned for your application via the developer portal

### Retrieve Airport [GET]

+ Response 200

   + Headers

